The dawn of that inevitable day , When wrapped in shrouded clay their warmest friend The widowed virtues shall again deplore , When over his urn in pious grief shall bend His Britain , and bewail one patriot more ; For soon must thou , too soon ! who spreadest abroad Thy beaming emanations unconfined , Doomed , like some better angel sent of God To scatter blessings over humankind , Thou too must fall , OH Pitt ! to shine no more , And tread these dreadful paths , a Faulkland trod before
